navigation_text: Face towards the shop with the blue awning, so that the shop with the rainbow awning is slightly to your left. Go forward a bit, then go left to turn on the street that runs between those two shops. Walk down that street until you get to the intersection where the rainbow stripes are on your left and the blue awning is on your right. There will be a fork in the road in front of you. Take the left fork. You will pass a couple of bikes parked on your right, and scaffolding on your left. Continue on, passing a tree with an orange net around its base on your left. You will also pass a few red doors, and then you will see an intersection. Turn left at it. You will see some more red doors on your left. At the next intersection, turn left again. There will be a red building with black stairs on your right. Stop when you're right at the end of it.
Follow traffic to the light and go left. Stop just before reading the door with pillars on either side on the right, with two large white bins on either side of it. Rotate right.

Position yourself so you are standing right at the entrance to the intersection. There will be a white sign with a red and black symbol on a pole to your left and a building just ahead on the right that is green on top and bluish-gray on the bottom. Walk straight through the intersection directly in front of you and straight through the next one you come to, as well. After you pass these first two intersections, turn left at the third one you arrive at. After you turn, there will be a business on your right with all windows on the front and side and a blue, red, and white sign. When you get to the next intersection, turn left, but stop immediately.

Orient yourself so that the three green mailboxes are to your left. Go straight. There will be a bus stop to your left. Go past it. Take a right. Go straight and when you see bikes ahead toward the right, take another right. Go past all the rental bikes.

You're standing in the middle of an intersection. Position yourself so scaffolding is on your right and on your left is a food vendor. There will also be orange and white construction barrels in the left lane. You're going to take this street all the way to the first intersection. This is a long block. You'll pass a fenced in playground on your left when you're almost there. When you get to that intersection, turn left. After you turn, you'll see three small red flags extending from poles on the building to your right. Stop before you get to the next intersection. On your left is a business with a red sign next to a yellow business with a yellow and white sign.

Orient yourself so you are moving with the flow of traffic. Go past the orange and white barriers on the right. Turn right at the next intersection. Ahead you'll see more orange and white barriers and a fence on your right. Turn right at the next intersection. The middle of the street should have yellow tape, orange barriers and a light sign. Go down this street. Just past the grey trailer on your right, you'll see some orange barriers and more fencing.
Orient yourself so that the red deli awning is on your right. Go forward and then turn left at the intersection. Go straight until you see a parking garage on your right.

Go down this road the correct direction. When you get to the first intersection make a left turn. There is a brown storefront with orange on it on the left corner. Go straight one block. At the intersection make a left turn. There are blue bike rentals on your right side. Go one block then make another left turn. There will be some yellow on the right of you almost like stripe on the posts then on the left is a lot of blue. Go straight. As you go there is a blue wall to the left with some red doors. Stop on the sidewalk before you enter the intersection. Look to the right there are a lot of flowers.

Go in the same direction as traffic. There will be a blue awning up ahead on your left. Move forward to the first intersection. Turn left. You will be heading in the same direction as traffic. There will be scaffolding on your left. Proceed to the next intersection and turn left. There will be a building on your right with a bright orange awning. Proceed down this street until you see some yellow cones on your right. Stop right after you pass these cones. Turn to your right. You will see a black and yellow sign with people on it.

Go with traffic flow to the next intersection and turn left. Still with traffic flow, go to the next intersection and turn left. Again, with traffic flow, go all the way down and through the first intersection you come to. Just past the intersection on the right is a black hydrant with a silver top next to a silver pole.

Stand so you are moving with the flow of traffic. Move to the intersection and turn left. Continue to the next intersection. In the middle of the intersection, look right and there is an orange newspaper stand ahead to your right.

Orient yourself with traffic and proceed. Turn left at the first light. Turn left at the next light as well. Pass through the next light. Pass two fire hydrants on the left sidewalk as well as a bike post hoop. Then stop in front of a parking terminal.

Turn around so that you are facing the same direction as all the cars on your street. You should see a motorcycle parked on the left. Walk until you reach an intersection and then use the arrow to turn to your right. You should immediately see a woman in a black and yellow jacket about to enter a yellow SUV taxi. If you see her in front of you, walk straight, and then use the arrow that takes you straight through the intersection. You should see yellow sedan taxis in front of you. If you see a big red truck, you're on the wrong street, so just go back one step and use the other arrow. Now keep walking straight. go straight through the first intersection, towards two orange, diamond-shaped signs on the left side of the street. You should soon come into an intersection with black-and-white crosswalks. Stop here, and turn to your left, so that you are facing a building with a red and white sign. Take one step toward this building. A police officer in a yellow reflective jacket should appear in front of you. Take one more step, and then turn to your left again. The building with the red and white sign should now be on your right and a white van should be in front of you. Start walking down this street. Take about four or five steps, and you should see Touchdown the Bear above a green traffic light.

With the greenish wall to your right, go straight and take a right. Go straight until you reach a bus stop on the right; then take a right. Go straight until you reach (on the left) a pole, a tree, and a bright red awning with a silver awning next to it.

Turn yourself so you are facing the flow of traffic. Go straight. Go to the light and turn right. Continue straight down this one way street. Go straight through the first intersection. Continue straight until you reach another intersection with a light and turn right. Go straight until you see a faded painting of the word school on the road. Move straight so this word disappears under you and then on the left side of the road, you should see a painted bike on the road.

Put the green umbrellas on your left, and move forward with the flow of traffic. When you get to the first intersection, turn right. You should have a short red post now on your left. Move ahead with traffic. At the first intersection, continue straight. Directly after that, turn right in the main intersection. Now you'll have orange and white barriers on your left. Continue straight until you pass a blue wall on your right, with several garbage bins. Stop before entering the intersection.

Turn so the row of blue rental bikes is on your left. Move forward to the intersection right ahead of you, and turn right. You'll have construction scaffolding on your left now, and a red food truck on the right. Go forward to the next intersection and make another right. Now you'll be on a street with red-painted bus lanes on both sides of the road. Go forward to the next intersection (a three-way) and once again turn right. You'll now have a park on your left side. You'll soon pass a public toilet on the sidewalk to the left (looks like a small silver shed). Just past the toilet, you'll pass a row of benches. There's a gap, then a second stretch of benches. Stop when you're in line with the beginning of that second row of benches (so you're just past the gap in the benches.

Put the business with the red sign and white lettering to your left. Ahead on the right is a purple banner with a yellow square. Walk with the flow of traffic to the intersection ahead. At the intersection, turn right so that you have red awnings on your right. Walk down this road. When you get close to the intersection ahead, stop. On your right will be a cart with a blue umbrella. On the left will be a hot dog cart with red and yellow umbrellas. Come even with the red umbrella on the end of the cart.

Face the direction of traffic and go straight through the intersection. You will have a building on your right with archways and on your left the building with have green awnings. Go straight to the next light and take a left. Now you should have a right building on your right. Go straight. You will pass scaffolding on your right. Go to the intersection and take a left. There will be scaffolding on your right and a bank with blue on their windows on your left. Go straight to the light and go into the middle of the intersection. Look to your right and you will see a small tree in a pot on the corner in front of the building with light blue windows. There is a trash can to the right of the tree

Follow traffic to the light and go right. Continue on the cramped twisty road until passing the fruit and vegetable vendor on the right and reaching the next light. Go right. There'll be hedgerows to your left and a shop with a black sign band with white text and a blue banner with birds above it on your right. Stop when pass the scaffolding on your right and you're even with the road branching off to your right.

Align yourself with the small streets parked cars. There should be a phone booth on your right, as well as a storefront with blue doors. Head down to the next intersection, and make a left. Make another left at the next intersection, and keep in mind the orange diamond construction sign. Take a couple steps in to the road

Look for a black banner hanging from a flag pole with white letters on it. Keep the banner to your right and go with traffic. Turn right at the first intersection. Neon lights in the building on the corner. Keep straight pass the road work. Stop just pass the last green scaffolding to the right and next the the large gold rotating doors.

Go with the flow of traffic. When you reach the first intersection, turn left. There will be a building on your right where the first two stories are mostly glass. Go to the next intersection and turn left again. There will be a storefront with a yellow roof to your right. Go to the next intersection and turn left once last time. There will be a maroon awning to your right. Go to the next intersection and continue straight, but stop immediately after you exit the intersection. Turn slightly to your right.

With the white-tipped bell-shaped bollards to your right, go against traffic. When you reach the light, go left. You'll now be in the proper lane going with traffic. At the next light, go left, where you'll have a colorful fence in front of a playground to your left. Go through the light and stop just before passing the red double doors on your right. Rotate right.

Face the closest traffic light and continue past it, making a right at the next traffic light, where the black storefront is on your right. Move forward and make a left into the small alley, with the gray storefront now on your right. Move forward and quickly stop.

Orient yourself so you are moving with the flow of traffic. Head forward and pass the playground to the right. Turn left at the next intersection. To your right will be a yellow storefront with brownish red trimmed doors/windows. Head forward and make a left at the next intersection as well. You will see a red brick building on the right. and some light greened trim on the left. Head down passing the long row of blue bikes on the left, stopping just short of the intersection crosswalk. On your right are two yellow poles.

Look for the large image of a woman on the building and the orange awing on the right, go in this direction. Turn left at the first intersection. Paid parking will be on the right. Go straight at the right turn only. Turn left at the left turn only. A line of blue bikes will be on the left. Turn left again at the next intersection. Look right. Stop slightly pass the large face painted on the building and next to the bike on the green pole with red sign.

Go in the same direction as traffic. Move forward to the first intersection. Turn right. You will be heading in the same direction as traffic. Move forward through two intersections. When you come to the third, turn right. There will be a park on your right and some diagonal parking on your left. Move forward just slightly until on the left you see a break in the diagonal parking and fenced in parking lots on both on your left and right. Turn to your right. You'll see a fenced in grassy area with a red pole in it.

Turn so that the buildings are on your right and a road on your left Proceed to the first street and turn right. Go to the stop sign and turn right again then make another right as soon as you can. On your left you will see a gate for a parking lot

Turn and follow with the traffic.There are some flags hanging on side of buildings on the right. Bike parking on the left. Turn right at the intersection. Turn right at next intersection. Flags hanging on both sides of street on buildings.

Turn to face in the same direction as traffic. You'll be looking at an arch up ahead. Walk forward under the arch. The road will start to fork - take the left side up to the intersection. You're essentially going to make a U turn to come back down the road. Now you'll have the arch on your left. As you get close to it, slow. When you can't see the arch on the other side, but you can see the two columns closest to you, stop.

Turn so the empty bike rental slots are to your right side. Make a left turn at the intersection. At the first intersection with a large red awning up on the left side corner keep going straight. When you get to the next intersection go straight again. At the next intersection make a left turn. Go a short distance then stop. You should still be on the crosswalk. Look to the right and there is a mailbox and phone just slightly ahead of you.

Orient yourself with traffic, proceed to the light and then turn left. Turn left at the next light too. Pass the barricades on the right. Stop after passing over a speed bump. There is a bright red door to the right.

Follow the flow of traffic, where the scaffolding is to your right and a silver building on your left, and make a left at the first intersection. There will now be construction on your left and brown and white awning on your right. Follow the traffic, make a left and stop at the corner with the construction on your left and red signage on the store to your right.

Follow the flow of traffic and go forward. Turn right at the intersection. Continue forward and merge onto the road. As you continue there will be a road to your right with a white van and some traffic cones to the left.

Turn and enter into the street with the green bike path on the left and go forward in the same direction traffic is flowing. Turn right at the next intersection and continue left at the split. Turn right at the next street between 2 trash cans. There will be trees on the left side of the street. You will pass 4 trees on the left.

You are standing in the middle of an intersection. Rotate until you are facing down the street with traffic moving through the intersection. Make sure you are facing forward with the forward direction of the flow of traffic. Proceed forward to the next intersection. Turn left at the intersection. Proceed forward to the next intersection. Turn left at the intersection. This will be needlessly complicated. Proceed forward to the next intersection. Turn left at the intersection Proceed forward a short distance. To your right, you will see a number of black cables running into a white object on the sidewalk. If you pass these cables, you have gone too far and should turn back. To the left of the black cables, you will see a black painted fire hydrant between two short metal posts.

Orient yourself so that you are facing the same way as the parked cars. Go past two 3-way intersections; when you get to the 4-way intersection, turn left. A gas station will be on your right. Go down this street. Turn left but then immediately stop. You should still be standing in the middle of the intersection, basically. If you are not already doing so, face the row of blue bikes.

Head in the direction of traffic. Turn left at the intersection. Keep going straight until you have just passed the building with graffiti all over the side on your right. To your left will be two green bags sitting next to a small tree.

Turn so the pointed black awning is on your left. Follow the flow of traffic down this road and turn left at the intersection. Still moving with traffic, follow this road a short way and turn left at the intersection. On this corner there is a yellow awning on your right and a black awning on your left. Follow this road to the next intersection and turn left again. Stop just after you enter this road and look to your right. There is a store with a burgundy sign. At the left corner of that sign there is a small metallic circular sign hanging to the left of a tree and right of the black store to the left.

Follow the flow of traffic to the intersection. Turn right. Stay on this road. Go through 2 intersections. Turn right at the 3rd. Go forward a little bit. There is a sign on the right with a person in a red triangle (Right side of street).
Follow traffic, with the shop with the yellow sign band with red and green glyphs to your left. Go right at the light, and right again at the next one. Stop after the red awning, and rotate left.

Orient yourself so that you are facing the intersection. Go straight through the intersection. Continue to the next intersection, the one with the big billboard done in white and red dots. Turn left here so that there is a billboard up ahead on the right with basketball players on it. Go straight through the next intersection and stop immediately after you cross the second crosswalk. Turn to your left. There are two bins sitting next to one another, one green and one blue.
Turn and go in the direction with the traffic. Turn left at intersection. Red umbrellas to the right. Turn left at intersection.

Turn against the flow of traffic. Take a slight right, and continue on the right side of the road. Take the first left and continue onto the little road. Then take the next left. On the left by the basketball court you will see a red bike. Stop to where the bike is hidden behind the car.

Turn to face the intersection. Go straight through the intersection. Keep going straight until you reach the next intersection, then turn left. Just after you turn, you'll see a round blue bus sign with a deli on your left and a grocery store on your right.

Go with traffic. (behind the white van) Turn right at the first intersection. Turn right again at the next intersection. (down the one way behind the yellow van) Keep straight. On the right, Stop when you see a blue bike locked up on the corner. (the bike should still be in front of you.)

Align yourself on the larger road, with the flow of traffic, there should be a yellow, red and orange newspaper stand on your left. Head through this first intersection straight and make a left at the second, where and orange sign will be on the corner. Head down this intersection until you can make a right turn and stop, to your left should be a yellow bike,

Face the same direction of the cars and pass the yellow pedestrian sign that is on your right. Go down the street, passing the parks and make a right at the intersection. Pass the tan building on your right and make a right at the intersection, with the white storefront on your right. Continue down the street, passing the yellow bars on the right and stopping before you reach the steps leading to the entrance of the brown building.

Follow the flow of traffic down the narrow road until you get to the next intersection and keep forward. You are going to go onto another narrow road. At the next intersection you will see all the construction stuff on the left. Take this left. Go up to the next intersection past the scaffholding and take a left. Now go forward until the next intersection and you will see orange and grey construction stuff on the left and more scaffholding.

face so that you are moving with the flow of traffic and go to the 1st intersection take a right and continue down to the next intersection, stop on the zebra crossing, you will have scaffolding to your right and on your left there is a manhole half on the sidewalk and half in the road

Head in the direction of traffic . At the intersection make a right turn into the one way road. Keep on moving forward passing all the construction work till you arrive at another intersection in which you want to head straight to the other end of the road. Head forward till you notice a building that provide parking service on your right and a photography store on your left. A few steps forward you should be In front of a building with a glass door on your right and a notice a bike leaning on a pole.

Begin by traveling with the flow of traffic. Turn left at the first intersection. Turn left at the next intersection. After you turn, you'll see a building with large windows and a blue signs. At the next intersection, make another left turn, so three left turns in total. Right before you reach another intersection with a one-way road, you'll see a green trash bin on the corner to your right.

Turn so you are facing a makeshift built box with chain link fence around it. Go straight into the narrow street. Continue past the chain link fence on the left. It's a long road, there will be a long red awning on the right. At the intersection past that turn left. On the left side before getting to the chain linked parking lot, there is a black and white fire hydrant. with two poles on either side of it.

Start with the flow of the traffic. You should have a brown truck to your right and a white one to your left. Go until you hit the intersection and take a left. Go to the next intersection and take a left. Before you go down the road, you should see a bank building on the left and in front of you there are a bunch of white vans. Follow this until you pass all the white vans on the left and you see this black truck.

Turn so you are travelling with traffic. Move up the block and go left at the first intersection. As you move up the block, you should see a orange and white construction barrier on your left. When you pass the construction, just before you reach the next intersection look straight ahead, towards the intersection. Across the way, you will see two concrete posts in front of a single tree.

Go with traffic. Turn left at the first intersection. Orange and white road barriers will be on the left. Turn left again at the next intersection, more barriers on the left. Stop just pass the orange and white cone with an orange flag in it. Look ahead of you

Stand so you are moving with the flow of traffic, out of this intersection. You should now have a bright orange building to your right. Move straight until you reach the next intersection and turn right. Continue until you come to a large blue dumpster-type structure. Move past it and turn back to face it. On the side is a large white sign.

Align yourself with the flow of parked cars traffic. Keep left with the road, and at the next left, take it, then another immediate left, to make a u-turn. A few steps down you'll see a fire hydrant and a moped parked next to it with a brown seat.

Orient yourself so the park is on your right. Take a side step to the right so you're fully into the intersection. Now go straight to the next intersection, keep the park on your right. At this intersection, your goal is to to your right. In order to do that, you'l basically have to turn around to see the road you're going down. Turn until you see a road that will keep the park on your right. Go down that road to the next intersection. Again, you want to turn right which involves basically turning all the way around. The goal is to keep the park on your right again. Pass the weird white triangle based awning on your right at the entrance to the park, and keep going straight. Just before you reach the next intersection, on your left near the road should be a black hydrant with a white top, between two red poles.

From the starting position, turn around so you are facing in the same direction as the flow of traffic. Move down the street in this direction until you get to a street light. Turn left at the light, where you'll see a sign with white letters. Move a good distance down the street until you get to an intersection. At the intersection, turn left. Instantly after you turn left you'll see a subway station sign, and a stairwell down on your right -- kind of at the corner of the intersection.

Follow the flow of traffic, passing two small intersections. Make a right at the traffic light, where the blue sign with the white letters are on your left. Go down the street where the trees are on your left and the black sign with white letters and blue/white squiggles are on the right. Follow the traffic and make a right once you pass the scaffolding. The park is on your left now. Stop when you reach the blue store awning by the alley way on your right.

Align yourself with the flow of traffic so that the trees are on your left and the sidewalk on your right. Head straight through the first intersection and make a right at the next. You should be in front of a green awning on your left after you turn. Head down this street to make another right, just before the next intersection on your left, you'll see a wide red awning over the entrance with two smaller ones over the windows.

Turn so you are travelling with the flow of traffic. At the first intersection you come to, go right. Go up the block and hang another right at the next intersection. You should see some trees ahead. As you go watch the right side, you are getting close when you see the large orange brick building with black trim. When you pass this building, the next building should be a brown brick building. Stop when you reach the entrance of that brown building.

Align yourself with the flow of traffic, and head down to the intersection. Make a right here. Head down shortly to the next intersection, and make another right. Going forward a bit, you should see a silver and black hydrant with two posts on either side of it, on your left.

Orient yourself so you are going in the same direction as the white van in the middle of the intersection. Continue straight ahead until you reach the next intersection. At this intersection, take a right. There will be a business with large yellow and red signage on your right. Continue forward until you reach the next intersection. Take a right and go forward a tiny bit. On your right, you will see a business with a blue sign. To the right of that building is the doors to an apartment building. There are red columns and it says Columbia above the door.

There's a business on your left with large red letters, go with the flow of traffic. Turn left at this intersection. Go all the way down this street and turn left at the next intersection. There will be some scaffolding to your right. Go to the next intersection and turn left and stop.

Turn around and align yourself with the flow of traffic up this street. You may have to make a slight right to keep going up this street. Ignore the first intersection, and continue to the end of the road. Make a left at the end of the road, and do a u turn, making another left immediately. A few steps down you should see a white sign with weird circles and lines behind two pick up trucks.

Follow the flow of traffic, with the red banners to your right, going through this first intersection and making a left at the next one. There will now be a grassy median to your right. Go against traffic and make your last left at the intersection. Continue past the little garden in front of the black awning on your left and stop after passing the first green awning on your right, before reaching the first tri-colored flag to your left.

Go in the same direction as the FedEx truck. Turn left at the first intersection. Pass next intersection. Turn left at the next intersection. You will see a FedEx truck. Make a left at the next intersection Shorty after turning,on your left side. You will see a blue motorcycle between two cars(suvs)

Turn so scaffolding is on your right and barriers with orange fencing is on your left. Go to the next corner about a block down and turn left. Now barriers are on your right and green construction walls to your left. Go to the next corner and turn left. When you turn there is chain link fencing on your right with truck trailers parked in it. Go past those, go past the big white signs on the fencing on the right, go past the pole with the square red sign on the right, and stop just beyond the parking lot where another fenced in area begins on the right. Go just a bit down from that and watch to your left to see a hydrant on the left side
Follow the flow of traffic to the next intersection. Turn right. At the next intersection, turn right again. Continue forward. Stop when you are just in front of the tractor (Orange/yellow).

Turn around so that you are facing the same direction as the cars on your street. You should see a diamond shaped yellow sign and a square yellow sign on a pole to your left. Walk forward and stop in the middle of the first intersection you come to. Turn to your right when you are in the intersection, and start to walk down a narrow road that has a little cafe with green awnings on the right. Stop in the middle of the next intersection. Turn to your right, and you should be facing down another narrow street. This one has red brick buildings on both sides. The building on the left also has a red awning, and a green mailbox on the sidewalk in front of it. Walk down this narrow road. Pass some pumpkins on the steps to your right. You are about halfway down the road. You will approach an intersection, where the road on your right has been blocked by cones. In spite of this, walk down that road anyway. Your view might be blocked by a big green truck, but use the arrows to walk right through it. Walk down this road and you will come to an intersection with two red hexagon signs. Walk into the middle of that intersection, stop, and look around. On your left there will be a red post with lots of old stickers on it.

You are on a one way road, go with the flow of traffic. Make a right at the next intersection. There will be a park to your left. You will quickly come to a three way intersection, make a right. You will now have red brick buildings on both sides of you, continue straight and you will see a sign hanging on the right that is white with black, go past this sign and you will see to your left a red brick building with horizontal white striping and next to it a yellow brick building. Stop right where these two buildings meet. Turn to the left to look at these buildings, the yellow building has lamps on both sides of the door.

Orient yourself so the blue bikes are on your right. Go forward to the intersection and turn left. Walk down this street, and continue straight through the first intersection. Go Straight through the next three way intersection. At the next four way intersection, where there is a subway entrance on your right, turn left. Follow the traffic, continuing straight through the three way intersection, and straight through the four way intersection, stopping as soon as you're through it. On the right, just before a tall building filled with scaffolding will be a red square sign with white markings on it.

You are moving with traffic, there is an intersection right in front of you, take a right here. there is scaffolding on the right, and then you will find a parking garage on the left. Continue to the next intersection. Take a right at this intersection, you will see a bright green store sign on your right with a half apple on it. continue to the next intersection, at this intersection take a right. there is a black building with gold doors on the right, head down this street. You will pass a large poster with a woman in a black dress laying on red letters. On your left is a building with xmas lights and wreaths.

From your starting point, turn around so that you are facing the same direction as the cars on your street. The playground should be on your left and the blue awning should be on your right. Move forward, keeping the playground on your left. It will be a long straight walk for a while, but if you pass a yellow awning with red foreign characters on your right, you are on the right track, and can just keep moving. Just follow the road until you come to a four way intersection. Take a right at this intersection. You should now be walking between a light-red stone building with turquoise doors and a shop with brown awnings over shuttered windows. Walk straight through the first intersection you come to. As you pass onto the other side, the building with the shiny silver sign with red letters and blue foreign characters should still be on your left. If you are properly situated, just keep moving forward. You will pass a purple, pink, and blue umbrella on your left shortly thereafter. Walk forward a bit further, and before you enter another intersection (where a shop with fruit stands and a blue sign with red characters should be on your right) stop between two red hexagon signs on poles.

Turn with the flow of traffic and head to the newest intersection. Turn right, then take the next right. There will be a vendor on the right side with blue and yellow umbrellas. Pass orange ladder, and continue. On the left there is a tall green scaffolding. Stop at the very end of it/ There is a bike (Left side) chained to a pole with a pink paper.

Head down the street with the orange and white barriers on your left. Go straight through the first intersection. When you reach the next intersection, take a right. Go straight through the next intersection you come to. Stop immediately.

Turn and go in the same direction of the traffic. Go to the intersection and turn right. Red awning to the right. You will pass on the right a red awning with yellow.Turn right at next intersection. 3 Red awnings on the right. Stop at the last one

With the islands with bell-shaped bollards on your right, go to the light, against traffic. Go right enough that you're going in the same direction, but in the proper lane, with traffic. The bell-shaped bollards and concrete island now on your left and scaffolding ahead on your right. Go through the next intersection, but stop before you reach the crosswalk. On the green wall to your right will be a black sign with 5 white arrows on it.

Hello. Please orient yourself with the orange construction cones on your left side and the tall stone wall on your right side. You will see an underpass up ahead with a green sign and white letters. You will be inside a long tunnel for now. Walk straight through it until you see daylight and approach an intersection. At the intersection, you will see a light brown brick building with large windows and gray garage door. Turn right here. There will be orange and white construction cones on your left side with two white vans ahead of you. Move straight in between the white vans until you just pass in front of them. Look towards your left side. You will see a white delivery truck with the back doors open.

Go in the direction of the rental bike racks, straight the the next intersection. There should be two red tiers of awnings ahead. Take a left at the intersection, and go to the next intersection, the one with a blue awning to the right. Take a left. There are big green rectangles on the store to your left.

Hello there! 1. Orient yourself so that you're going with the flow of traffic. There should be a blue storefront to your left. 2. When you reach the first intersection, there should be some construction ahead of you and to your right. Take a left here, and the construction should now be behind you. 3. Take another left at the next intersection. Upon reorienting yourself, there should be a business with brown awnings and several tables and chairs outside to your left and a court to your right. 4. Move forward for a while until you're almost at the next intersection. Stop when you're in the middle of the crosswalk. If you look to your left, you should see three red umbrellas.

Turn and go with the flow of traffic. Head to the nearest intersection. Turn right. Continue down this street, and take the next right, followed by the next right. This one is strange because its almost like a backwards turn and then a right. There should be a green covered walkway on the left. Continue into the next intersection. Just before you are given the option for a 4 way turn look at the smoke.

With the chainlink fence on your right and building to your left, go to and through the next two lights. After passing the second, watch for green benches on your left; just after passing them, look right, to see a cement walkway between two black fences on your right. Stop when you're even with that path.

Face the flow of traffic and move straight. Take a right at the first intersection. there is now a mail truck on your left. Go straight. After a while there will be a large truck in front of you. When you can see the back left side of the tire

You're going to want to go in the flow of traffic. There should be a black SUV in front of you. Keep going forward, you will pass a truck, and some orange cones will come up. You will hit an intersection and you need to turn right. As you take that right, there will be a red store on the right, a drink shop on the left and you should be behind a bus. Go past all the scaffolding and take a right. You should see a food stand and now you are in the middle of a bunch of scaffolding. You will come up just besides the red white and blue delivery truck. ANd in front of that will be a brown delivery truck.

Turn so the blue construction is on your right. Follow traffic down this road to the first intersection and turn left. You'll now have a brown brick building on your left with some construction in front of it. Follow this road, passing the first intersection and stopping just after you pass the brown brick church building on the left.
face the direction of the traffic with the scaffolding on the left. Go to the end of the street and make a right. Go down that street and stop before you get the the yellow newspaper box.

Step into the intersection that's immediately in front of you and turn right. After you turn a dark red awning with white lettering will be on your right. The business also has an A-frame sign in front of it and neon signs in the windows of the second floor. At the first light, turn right. There's an outdoor space with vendors to your left now. A few steps ahead is the next intersection. turn right there. You might feel like you change scenes for a minute, but you'll get back to where you need to be if you keep straight. When you see a red and white bulls-eye on your left then you're at your final intersection. Go straight through the intersection and stop. Turn back around and take a few steps to your left front corner (where you just came from). There's a green mailbox there with graffiti on it.

Position yourself so rental bikes are on your left and a chain fence is on your right. There is an intersection directly in front of you. Turn right at this intersection. There will now be green scaffolding on your right. and a blue bridge up ahead. When you get to that bridge, you'l be turning left onto a one-way street. There will be an outdoor market with goods for sale on both sides of you. The road you're on will end just ahead, so you can only go left or right. Here, you will turn left. When you get to the next intersection, you will make another left turn. A black and gray building with a long red awning will be on your left after you turn. Go straight through the first intersection you get to on this road. At the second intersection you get to, stop at the crosswalk (so you don't walk through it).

Go with traffic flow, with the rental bikes to your left and scaffolding to your right down this long block and through the first intersection you come to. Go past the black framed windows on the right, past the tan fire escapes on the right, past the American flag on the right, down to the last of 4 brown awnings on your left and stop.
Turn and go with the flow of traffic at the third traffic light turn left.At the next traffic light turn left and stop.

Follow the flow of traffic, with the white building on your left and make a right at the intersection. Pass the blue storefronts on your left and make your last right at the intersection. Continue down this one way street, passing the brown apartment buildings on your right and stop before passing the fenced play area on your left. Just past the fence, there is a cross on the brick building.

Turn so the elevated road is to your left and the brick buildings are on your right. Go to the next corner and turn left. Go under the elevated road to the next corner and turn left again. Go down this road and keep going straight, past the yellow pedestrian sign on the right beyond the 3-way corner. Just go straight here. At the next corner on the upper right corner is a building with a red door. Go through this intersection. Go down to where you can see the last 3 cars parked diagonally on the right in front of you. Turn to your left

Face the direction of the traffic and go straight. Go to the first intersection and make a right. Go straight and pass the first traffic light. Keep going until you reach the green scaffolding next to the black store canopy

Align yourself with the flow of traffic, and head to the intersection, to make a left. You'll head down a long road, where you'll make another left. Shortly after, you'll make one more left.
